that this is a current affairs piece,
not entertainment.

54
00:04:02,076 --> 00:04:04,995
He'll end up at his father-in-law's
JARIM Apparel anyway.

55
00:04:05,079 --> 00:04:07,665
How is this entertainment?
Am I wrong, Se-yeong?

56
00:04:07,748 --> 00:04:09,917
Are you seriously asking me?

57
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:13,504
You need a top actress to blow it up.

58
00:04:13,587 --> 00:04:16,632
He's just upset.
You really think he doesn't know?

59
00:04:16,715 --> 00:04:18,634
Why ask if he already knows?

60
00:04:18,717 --> 00:04:20,928
He just wants comfort, got it?

61
00:04:21,011 --> 00:04:24,682
"I did my best.
It wasn't me who ruined Ji-woo's life."

62
00:04:24,765 --> 00:04:27,267
This isn't the first time
her life's been ruined.

63
00:04:27,351 --> 00:04:28,852
And she's firm.

64
00:04:28,936 --> 00:04:31,814
Meanwhile, unsteady Kyeong-do
is pouring a morning drink.

65
00:04:33,691 --> 00:04:36,110
Se-yeong, you know
I quit drinking when I was 30.

66
00:04:36,193 --> 00:04:39,530
Why did you call us
if you're only going to talk to Se-yeong?

67
00:04:39,613 --> 00:04:43,242
Hey, punk, because Se-yeong is
the most reasonable among us, you idiot.

68
00:04:43,325 --> 00:04:45,786
- Are you saying I'm…
- Hey, will you shut up?

69
00:04:47,705 --> 00:04:48,831
Are you going to drink?

70
00:04:58,007 --> 00:04:59,008
Kyeong-do.

71
00:05:00,009 --> 00:05:00,968
- Are you scared?
- I am.

72
00:05:01,051 --> 00:05:02,761
- You want me to call her?
- No.

73
00:05:03,262 --> 00:05:04,972
Don't you do that, Se-yeong.

74
00:05:05,055 --> 00:05:08,684
And by chance, if she calls you,
don't give her my number.

75
00:05:08,767 --> 00:05:09,977
You know that, right--

76
00:05:15,899 --> 00:05:17,276
What's up with this timing?

77
00:05:18,986 --> 00:05:20,195
MANAGER JIN HAN-KYEONG

78
00:05:20,279 --> 00:05:22,031
Oh, it's the department manager.

79
00:05:23,073 --> 00:05:23,991
Hello?

80
00:05:24,575 --> 00:05:26,326
What? Okay.

81
00:05:29,163 --> 00:05:29,997
Bye.

82
00:05:30,539 --> 00:05:31,957
- You're leaving?
- What?

83
00:05:32,041 --> 00:05:34,668
- After calling us all here?
- My work is calling me back.

84
00:05:34,752 --> 00:05:36,879
I turned back from a business trip
to see you.

85
00:05:39,048 --> 00:05:40,507
Gosh.

86
00:05:49,850 --> 00:05:50,809
What?

87
00:05:50,893 --> 00:05:53,604
I heard you had soju with your breakfast.

88
00:05:53,687 --> 00:05:56,690
- So?
- You won't even have a beer with us.

89
00:05:56,774 --> 00:05:59,443
- I'm disappointed.
- Didn't you hear? It was just a bottle.

90
00:05:59,526 --> 00:06:01,653
Why order it if you won't drink it?

91
00:06:01,737 --> 00:06:03,655
- By the way--
- No personal questions.

92
00:06:04,573 --> 00:06:07,785
Please go to a sauna,
or at least the shower room.

93
00:06:07,868 --> 00:06:09,828
You smell like a widower. Okay?

94
00:06:12,706 --> 00:06:13,707
What is this?

95
00:06:13,791 --> 00:06:15,375
Return to your seat

96
00:06:15,459 --> 00:06:18,545
and enjoy watching
the surprised emojis on your article.

97
00:06:18,629 --> 00:06:19,755
Okay.

98
00:06:21,423 --> 00:06:25,302
An article on An Da-hye
made him drink soju.

99
00:06:27,387 --> 00:06:28,680
Did you date An Da-hye?

100
00:06:33,519 --> 00:06:35,896
I've seen many stuck on their first love,

101
00:06:35,979 --> 00:06:38,524
but you're the only one
who couldn't move on for 18 years.

102
00:06:38,607 --> 00:06:40,234
Am I right, Lee Kyeong-do?

103
00:06:40,317 --> 00:06:42,820
You're making up a story.

104
00:06:42,903 --> 00:06:46,532
You're not worried
about An Da-hye or her affair.

105
00:06:46,615 --> 00:06:47,533
Stop it, seriously.

106
00:06:47,616 --> 00:06:50,077
Did you drink soju in the morning

107
00:06:50,160 --> 00:06:53,497
because you were worried about
the wife of An Da-hye's man?

108
00:06:56,625 --> 00:06:57,751
It's humanism.

109
00:06:59,545 --> 00:07:01,046
Hey, did you date Seo Ji-woo?

110
00:07:01,130 --> 00:07:02,214
Use my title, idiot.

111
00:07:02,297 --> 00:07:04,758
Assistant Manager,
did you really date Seo Ji-woo?

112
00:07:05,259 --> 00:07:07,886
Have you ever bitten this before?
Try it today.

113
00:07:07,970 --> 00:07:09,429
You know what happens then?

114
00:07:09,513 --> 00:07:11,431
He'll write an article with his fingers.

115
00:07:11,515 --> 00:07:12,391
Go to a sauna.

116
00:07:15,519 --> 00:07:16,353
What is that?

117
00:07:16,436 --> 00:07:19,064
- Go away. Go. Seriously.
- Okay.

118
00:07:31,994 --> 00:07:33,579
Intern, aren't you going home?

119
00:07:34,371 --> 00:07:35,789
I'm about to.

120
00:07:35,873 --> 00:07:36,707
Yeah?

121
00:07:52,598 --> 00:07:53,974
SEO JI-WOO

122
00:08:01,523 --> 00:08:03,150
JARIM APPAREL'S SEO JI-WOO

123
00:08:13,202 --> 00:08:17,998
SPRING, 2007

124
00:08:19,458 --> 00:08:20,292
Hello?

125
00:08:22,836 --> 00:08:26,256
How do I wait for an hour?
There's nothing but buildings here.

126
00:08:28,008 --> 00:08:29,468
Oh, I don't know.

127
00:08:30,677 --> 00:08:33,555
Call me when you're off then. Bye.

128
00:08:58,622 --> 00:08:59,623
What the…

129
00:09:00,749 --> 00:09:01,583
Where did it go?

130
00:09:09,049 --> 00:09:09,967
What the heck?

131
00:09:12,344 --> 00:09:13,178
What are you doing?

132
00:09:13,929 --> 00:09:16,348
- I lost a 500-won coin.
- Just come already.

133
00:09:16,431 --> 00:09:18,934
But I need that
for a banana-flavored milk.

134
00:09:19,017 --> 00:09:21,103
Why did it have to be a 500-won coin?

135
00:09:21,186 --> 00:09:22,521
Gosh.

136
00:09:25,107 --> 00:09:26,191
Hurry up!

137
00:09:30,570 --> 00:09:31,446
Damn it.

138
