140
00:10:23,123 --> 00:10:26,209
JUWON UNIVERSITY CLUB FESTIVAL

141
00:10:30,505 --> 00:10:34,134
All students of Juwon,
join the comedy club!

142
00:10:46,480 --> 00:10:47,606
You over there.

143
00:10:50,484 --> 00:10:52,027
- Me?
- Decided which club to join yet?

144
00:10:52,778 --> 00:10:54,696
I'm not joining any club.

145
00:10:55,489 --> 00:10:56,573
Okay.

146
00:10:57,616 --> 00:10:59,826
Then why don't you come
and have a seat here?

147
00:11:05,457 --> 00:11:07,876
Oh, it's an acting club?

148
00:11:07,959 --> 00:11:09,586
Once you hear the history of Chaos--

149
00:11:09,669 --> 00:11:11,213
I'm not into acting.

150
00:11:11,296 --> 00:11:13,090
Oh, actually, neither am I.

151
00:11:13,173 --> 00:11:14,174
Have a good day.

152
00:11:14,257 --> 00:11:16,259
Not so fast. You can't just leave.

153
00:11:17,427 --> 00:11:18,261
What?

154
00:11:19,596 --> 00:11:21,848
Will you sit here just for five minutes?

155
00:11:23,433 --> 00:11:24,267
Me?

156
00:11:26,686 --> 00:11:30,023
Because I have to go poop,
and I can't leave here unattended.

157
00:11:30,107 --> 00:11:31,358
Can you stay here for a second?

158
00:11:31,441 --> 00:11:33,860
Well, that is kind of…

159
00:11:33,944 --> 00:11:36,071
Oh, my stomach.

160
00:11:37,114 --> 00:11:40,367
You know if I end up pooping here,
I won't just let it slide, okay?

161
00:11:40,450 --> 00:11:42,452
But I'm just a passerby…

162
00:11:42,536 --> 00:11:45,163
If anyone comes,
give the application form to them.

163
00:11:45,247 --> 00:11:46,248
- But…
- Thanks!

164
00:11:47,416 --> 00:11:48,625
Oh, I almost pooped.

165
00:12:00,220 --> 00:12:04,850
If it's an acting club,
do you put on a play too?

166
00:12:06,309 --> 00:12:09,229
Don't tell me… A newbie?

167
00:12:10,147 --> 00:12:13,024
What makes you say "Don't tell me"?

168
00:12:13,942 --> 00:12:15,152
Do you need a mirror?

169
00:12:19,197 --> 00:12:20,699
- Fill it out.
- What?

170
00:12:20,782 --> 00:12:22,033
CHAOS CLUB APPLICATION FORM

171
00:12:22,951 --> 00:12:24,494
You just told me to look in the mirror.

172
00:12:24,578 --> 00:12:26,663
I meant you look old
for your age, not ugly.

173
00:12:26,746 --> 00:12:28,540
You're perfect for the lead role.

174
00:12:33,295 --> 00:12:37,883
You have a weird way of talking.

175
00:12:46,558 --> 00:12:48,685
NAME - LEE KYEONG-DO

176
00:12:49,352 --> 00:12:54,107
Your name is Lee Kyeong-do?
As in latitude and longitude?

177
00:12:57,360 --> 00:13:00,447
Journalism and broadcasting major?
Want to be a producer?

178
00:13:02,240 --> 00:13:05,035
Are you a senior? Why do you talk like--

179
00:13:07,120 --> 00:13:08,163
I got you one.

180
00:13:08,747 --> 00:13:10,081
Is it ultimately about beauty?

181
00:13:10,165 --> 00:13:12,334
I sat here for two days,
but I got nothing.

182
00:13:12,417 --> 00:13:14,544
Beauty? Who?

183
00:13:15,420 --> 00:13:16,755
How rude when we just met.

184
00:13:16,838 --> 00:13:18,924
You dropped the honorifics to me first.
Get a grip.

185
00:13:19,007 --> 00:13:23,303
Hey, why raise voices between newbies?

186
00:13:23,386 --> 00:13:24,221
A newbie?

187
00:13:24,304 --> 00:13:26,681
What? Did I say I was a senior?

188
00:13:29,601 --> 00:13:30,435
No.

189
00:13:30,519 --> 00:13:34,648
Then why are you making a damn fuss?
Bye now.

190
00:13:39,778 --> 00:13:42,405
All right. Write down your number.

191
00:13:42,489 --> 00:13:43,698
Let me catch her first.

192
00:13:43,782 --> 00:13:44,783
Hey.

193
00:13:45,367 --> 00:13:46,409
What?

194
00:13:48,453 --> 00:13:49,287
Are we done now?

195
00:13:49,371 --> 00:13:52,290
- No, no. Your email as well.
- What? Email? Email…

196
00:13:53,667 --> 00:13:56,253
- Are we done now? Bye.
- Yes, thanks.

197
00:13:56,336 --> 00:13:58,630
Good luck. I'll call you!

198
00:13:58,713 --> 00:13:59,923
A make-up class?

199
00:14:01,007 --> 00:14:03,510
Gosh, why are you studying so hard?

200
00:14:04,886 --> 00:14:06,304
Whatever, I'm leaving.

201
00:14:07,514 --> 00:14:09,140
I'll just see you in Apgujeong.

202
00:14:09,224 --> 00:14:10,267
Hey, newbie!

203
00:14:12,852 --> 00:14:15,730
Hey, but your school is pretty fun.
I'm hanging up.

204
00:14:19,526 --> 00:14:22,696
Hey, since you were rude to me,
you need to apologize.

205
00:14:22,779 --> 00:14:26,199
Let's face it. You look old.
I bet you hear that a lot.

206
00:14:28,493 --> 00:14:31,746
It's the first time.
And who are you to judge me?

207
00:14:32,914 --> 00:14:36,084
I was only expressing
what I saw and what I felt.

208
00:14:36,918 --> 00:14:38,670
You're getting unnecessarily angry.

209
00:14:40,338 --> 00:14:44,092
You're living in your own world.
Do you seriously think that?

210
00:14:46,761 --> 00:14:47,887
You're laughing?

211
00:14:50,515 --> 00:14:52,475
I'm bored. Do you want to grab a drink?

212
00:14:53,977 --> 00:14:56,396
Hey, don't you have common sense?

213
00:14:56,479 --> 00:15:01,276
So let's decide over a drink
if I'm clueless or if you indeed look old.

214
00:15:01,359 --> 00:15:04,487
Hey, the sun is still high up,
and I have a class.

215
00:15:04,571 --> 00:15:05,572
You're that upright?

216
00:15:05,655 --> 00:15:09,576
A student studying at school
isn't being upright, but it's a given.

217
00:15:10,493 --> 00:15:11,328
Oh, whatever.

218
00:15:12,412 --> 00:15:15,749
Latitude, longitude, Kyeong-do.
Let's make a globe together in peace.

219
00:15:15,832 --> 00:15:18,585
Hey, what's your name then? What's yours?

220
00:15:18,668 --> 00:15:21,296
After the first toast,
I'll show you my ID.

221
00:15:21,838 --> 00:15:24,966
By any chance, are you a light drinker?

222
00:15:29,554 --> 00:15:31,681
Hey. That's ridiculous.

223
00:15:31,765 --> 00:15:34,643
I could line up empty bottles
all the way to your house.

224
00:15:34,726 --> 00:15:35,560
Want to see?

225
00:15:35,644 --> 00:15:36,811
But I live in Busan.

226
00:15:39,356 --> 00:15:40,482
Your hometown?

227
00:15:41,149 --> 00:15:44,277
It's a lie, you idiot.
Let's go. I'll line up the bottles.

228
00:15:48,948 --> 00:15:50,200
Damn it.

229
00:15:53,370 --> 00:15:54,329
Cheers.

230
00:16:03,838 --> 00:16:05,507
I'm Ji-woo. Seo Ji-woo.

231
00:16:05,590 --> 00:16:06,424
What major?

232
00:16:13,098 --> 00:16:14,099
Cheers.

233
00:16:29,322 --> 00:16:30,323
English literature.

234
00:16:30,407 --> 00:16:32,826
Hey, did you retake the college exam
three times?

235
00:16:32,909 --> 00:16:34,911
You definitely seem older than me.

236
00:16:35,662 --> 00:16:37,288
I've looked like this since grade 7.

237
00:16:37,372 --> 00:16:39,666
This isn't Yonsei or Korea U.
Why repeat three times?

238
00:16:40,917 --> 00:16:43,795
Jeez, you sounded like my mom.
You're so fucking annoying.

239
00:16:43,878 --> 00:16:44,921
A penalty shot for you.

240
00:16:52,637 --> 00:16:53,471
Too much?

241
00:16:55,140 --> 00:16:56,766
I'll play along, kid.

242
00:17:06,234 --> 00:17:07,068
It's sweet.

243
00:17:08,278 --> 00:17:09,988
Excuse me. One more soju, please.

244
00:17:10,572 --> 00:17:11,823
It's so sweet.

245
00:17:21,040 --> 00:17:22,041
It's no use.

246
00:17:26,171 --> 00:17:28,256
The school shuttle
has stopped running for the night.

247
00:17:30,175 --> 00:17:32,761
Kyeong-do can't go home.

248
00:17:35,054 --> 00:17:36,389
Do you want me to sleep with you?

249
00:17:44,189 --> 00:17:45,023
Were you excited?

250
00:17:46,858 --> 00:17:48,067
See you.

251
00:17:52,781 --> 00:17:54,783
Gosh, seriously…

252
00:18:00,497 --> 00:18:01,331
Shit.

253
00:18:03,625 --> 00:18:06,252
Shit. That maniac, seriously.

254
00:18:15,094 --> 00:18:16,596
- Hey, Mr. Kim.
- Gosh.

255
00:18:19,307 --> 00:18:20,308
Go easy on the drinking.

256
00:18:24,604 --> 00:18:26,064
- Okay.
- Can you tell?

257
00:18:26,147 --> 00:18:28,525
Your booze smell's getting me drunk.
I'd fail a breath test.

258
00:18:29,943 --> 00:18:30,944
What about your car?

259
00:18:31,820 --> 00:18:33,279
My friend took it.

260
00:18:34,531 --> 00:18:37,700
Anyway, what were you doing here?

261
00:18:39,118 --> 00:18:40,787
You know Ha-yeong, right?

262
00:18:40,870 --> 00:18:43,331
- Your friend from the US?
- Yes, her.

263
00:18:43,414 --> 00:18:45,041
She goes to this school.

264
00:18:45,124 --> 00:18:47,710
I was here to meet her…

265
00:18:51,130 --> 00:18:54,050
Oh, but this school is so fun.

266
00:18:54,634 --> 00:18:57,387
- Should I go here instead?
- What about your school in the US?

267
00:18:58,680 --> 00:19:00,932
Oh, whatever. I'm going to sleep.

268
00:19:13,778 --> 00:19:15,572
Newbie. Hey.

269
00:19:19,242 --> 00:19:20,451
Oh, thank you.

270
00:19:20,535 --> 00:19:21,786
Let's go.

271
00:19:22,620 --> 00:19:24,038
What? Where?

272
00:19:24,122 --> 00:19:25,999
- Do you live on your own?
- No.

273
00:19:26,082 --> 00:19:28,126
- Are you taking a taxi?
- No.

274
00:19:28,793 --> 00:19:30,795
Then drink more!

275
00:19:30,879 --> 00:19:34,090
Let's go!

276
00:19:35,008 --> 00:19:38,428
Come with us. Let's go.

277
00:19:54,694 --> 00:19:55,570
Just go home, Woo-sik.

278
00:19:55,653 --> 00:19:57,906
Why crash in the club room? We have homes.

279
00:19:57,989 --> 00:20:00,700
And leave Kyeong-do alone?
Didn't I sound cool?

280
00:20:03,620 --> 00:20:05,038
Do I look old?

281
00:20:05,121 --> 00:20:06,039
You're helpless.

282
00:20:06,122 --> 00:20:07,457
That's why he's with us.

283
00:20:07,540 --> 00:20:09,250
What? Did someone say you look old?

284
00:20:10,376 --> 00:20:11,210
Was it a girl?

285
00:20:14,464 --> 00:20:15,298
No…

286
00:20:17,467 --> 00:20:19,177
Do you think she's interested in me?

287
00:20:19,260 --> 00:20:21,387
- But she said you look old.
- Yes.

288
00:20:21,471 --> 00:20:24,849
Can you tell a girl you're interested in
that she looks old?

289
00:20:25,433 --> 00:20:26,267
No.

290
00:20:32,690 --> 00:20:33,691
Were you excited?

291
00:20:34,442 --> 00:20:35,276
Shit…

292
00:20:37,028 --> 00:20:39,447
Hey, where are you going?
Senior, where are you going?

293
00:21:33,001 --> 00:21:34,752
Did you take care of the hangover?

294
00:21:36,754 --> 00:21:37,714
Get out of my sight.

295
00:21:38,548 --> 00:21:39,382
Let's go.

296
00:21:39,465 --> 00:21:42,927
Go… Hey, go where?
The class is about to start soon.

297
00:21:43,011 --> 00:21:45,221
- That's why we have to go now.
- Go where?

298
00:21:47,056 --> 00:21:48,307
Hey, hey, but…

299
00:22:05,324 --> 00:22:07,535
- Why are you doing this to me?
- I said, see you.

300
00:22:07,618 --> 00:22:09,996
This is too one-sided. What do you want?

301
00:22:10,079 --> 00:22:11,873
- Where did you sleep last night?
- Why care?

302
00:22:11,956 --> 00:22:13,499
- We're not strangers.
- Then what are we?

303
00:22:15,126 --> 00:22:17,170
We almost slept together.

304
00:22:17,253 --> 00:22:18,087
What?

305
00:22:21,758 --> 00:22:26,304
No. That's not true.
Are you out of your mind?

306
00:22:26,929 --> 00:22:30,016
Maybe I am. You look handsome to me.

307
00:22:30,600 --> 00:22:31,434
What?

308
00:22:35,104 --> 00:22:37,106
If you keep acting up, I'll get mad.

309
00:22:37,190 --> 00:22:38,191
You're so fucking cute.

310
00:22:38,274 --> 00:22:39,817
Oh, can't you speak without swearing?

311
00:22:39,901 --> 00:22:41,486
Where did you sleep?

312
00:22:41,569 --> 00:22:45,364
I slept in the club room with strangers
because of you.

313
00:22:45,448 --> 00:22:47,700
Did you join Chaos? I should join too.

314
00:22:48,701 --> 00:22:51,079
Don't, or I'm going to withdraw.

315
00:22:55,124 --> 00:22:57,919
- How many classes do you have today?
- Why do you ask?

316
00:22:58,002 --> 00:22:59,003
Mind your own business.

317
00:22:59,087 --> 00:23:00,630
- Let's drink.
- Drink?

318
00:23:00,713 --> 00:23:03,883
Hey, I feel like throwing up
whenever I see green because of you.

319
00:23:03,966 --> 00:23:05,176
I'll see you later.

320
00:23:05,259 --> 00:23:07,970
When your class is over,
is it 5 p.m.? 6 p.m.?

321
00:23:09,138 --> 00:23:10,473
See you in the club room.

322
00:23:10,556 --> 00:23:12,558
Gosh, get lost.

323
00:23:14,143 --> 00:23:15,812
- Stop talking back.
- Talking back…

324
00:23:19,273 --> 00:23:21,818
Jesus. That…

325
00:23:21,901 --> 00:23:23,277
Oh, I'm sorry.

326
00:23:30,159 --> 00:23:31,994
Damn it, she ordered two.

327
00:23:32,078 --> 00:23:36,374
All right, today, we talked about
how media affects our consciousness

328
00:23:36,457 --> 00:23:40,711
when we view it as a medium
and a technical ecology.

329
00:23:41,879 --> 00:23:47,093
By next class,
make sure to read Chapter 3,

330
00:23:47,677 --> 00:23:49,178
Authoritarian Media Theory.

331
00:23:49,262 --> 00:23:50,555
Yes, sir.

332
00:23:52,056 --> 00:23:54,809
It's over, you prick.
Have the candy and go home.

333
00:23:57,478 --> 00:23:59,689
Thank you.

334
00:24:02,316 --> 00:24:04,735
Oh, you're actually loyal.
You're pressuring us.

335
00:24:04,819 --> 00:24:06,779
Oh, drinking friends?
That's hard to resist.

336
00:24:06,863 --> 00:24:07,822
Are you down for a drink?

337
00:24:08,614 --> 00:24:10,241
- What? No.
- Then why are you here?

338
00:24:10,825 --> 00:24:11,659
Well…

339
00:24:12,952 --> 00:24:13,870
To become friends.

340
00:24:13,953 --> 00:24:15,580
Shit, that's so much pressure.

341
00:24:16,455 --> 00:24:18,791
What if your name were Wi-do?

342
00:24:18,875 --> 00:24:20,209
Kyeong-do is better.

343
00:24:25,256 --> 00:24:27,800
Why bother me smoking
when you've got nothing to do here?

344
00:24:27,884 --> 00:24:29,594
I'm okay. Feel free to smoke.

345
00:24:29,677 --> 00:24:33,723
How can I feel free?
Why don't you stop your fake cough?

346
00:24:35,600 --> 00:24:39,395
Well… Where are the other members?

347
00:24:39,478 --> 00:24:41,439
The three of us will do.

348
00:24:41,522 --> 00:24:42,398
Sorry?

349
00:24:42,481 --> 00:24:45,026
We got to secure
the club room again this year.

350
00:24:45,109 --> 00:24:48,029
We finally have a newbie.

351
00:24:48,112 --> 00:24:50,615
If one door closes,
another door opens, right?

352
00:24:50,698 --> 00:24:53,701
When we were just about to get kicked out,
we got a newbie.

353
00:24:53,784 --> 00:24:56,287
- Who brought him in?
- Right.

354
00:24:56,370 --> 00:25:01,542
So are you saying if I withdraw,
you're at risk of closing or something?

355
00:25:01,626 --> 00:25:03,419
Don't ask. It breaks my heart.

356
00:25:06,797 --> 00:25:08,925
Hey, this is awesome.
We'll get to put on a play.

357
00:25:09,008 --> 00:25:11,969
Hey, stamp the application form now.

358
00:25:12,053 --> 00:25:13,179
Stamp with your thumbprint.

359
00:25:13,262 --> 00:25:14,889
You were good at acting earlier.

360
00:25:18,726 --> 00:25:20,978
CURRENT AFFAIRS

361
00:25:35,326 --> 00:25:37,453
YOU'VE GOT A CALL
MOM

362
00:25:47,171 --> 00:25:48,422
Hello?

363
00:25:48,506 --> 00:25:50,716
<i>Ji-woo, what have you been up to lately?</i>

364
00:25:51,842 --> 00:25:55,179
Well, I'm out to meet a friend.

365
00:25:55,263 --> 00:25:58,224
This is why I told you
to stay in New York.

366
00:25:58,307 --> 00:26:00,893
Did you come back to waste your time?

367
00:26:04,230 --> 00:26:07,566
If you're going to take care of yourself,
do it properly.

368
00:26:08,484 --> 00:26:09,485
I'm hanging up.

369
00:28:41,345 --> 00:28:42,304
What are you doing here?

370
00:28:45,391 --> 00:28:47,518
What are you doing? It's dark.

371
00:28:49,186 --> 00:28:50,521
I'm listening to music.

372
00:28:52,314 --> 00:28:53,149
Aren't you going home?

373
00:28:54,900 --> 00:28:55,734
I will.

374
00:28:57,987 --> 00:28:58,821
Get up.

375
00:29:00,656 --> 00:29:01,490
Go first.

376
00:29:04,743 --> 00:29:07,746
Thought you were tough. What happened?
You sorry for breaking your promise?

377
00:29:10,749 --> 00:29:11,667
Did you wait for me?

378
00:29:13,919 --> 00:29:15,754
Am I crazy? Why would I wait for you?

379
00:29:15,838 --> 00:29:17,423
Then how do you know I didn't show up?

380
00:29:20,134 --> 00:29:21,135
Well…

381
00:29:22,636 --> 00:29:26,557
I had a club meeting. I had to be there.

382
00:29:27,224 --> 00:29:28,058
Got it?

383
00:29:40,529 --> 00:29:41,363
What?

384
00:29:41,947 --> 00:29:44,450
Do you want to listen to what I like?

385
00:29:47,328 --> 00:29:49,872
Whatever.
If you're not going, I'll go first.

386
00:29:49,955 --> 00:29:50,789
Okay.

387
00:29:57,630 --> 00:29:58,631
Gosh.

388
00:30:01,634 --> 00:30:02,885
It's dark here.

389
00:30:03,636 --> 00:30:06,388
The last bus will leave soon.
There'll be no one around.

390
00:30:07,056 --> 00:30:07,890
So?

391
00:30:07,973 --> 00:30:09,141
Get up. It's dangerous.

392
00:30:10,142 --> 00:30:11,143
Are you worried about me?

393
00:30:11,227 --> 00:30:12,895
Are you emotionally deprived?

394
00:30:12,978 --> 00:30:14,772
Why do you keep
giving meaning to everything?

395
00:30:38,754 --> 00:30:41,173
Wait, I mean, I…

396
00:30:42,925 --> 00:30:44,301
Well, I was just…

397
00:30:46,053 --> 00:30:47,304
Isn't my acting good?

398
00:30:48,305 --> 00:30:50,766
- Aren't I perfect for the acting club?
- Jeez…

399
00:30:54,019 --> 00:30:57,398
Oh, get a grip. Just get up.
The bus will leave soon.

400
00:31:00,818 --> 00:31:02,152
I'm good at swearing, right?

401
00:31:02,236 --> 00:31:03,404
Don't be proud of it.

402
00:31:03,487 --> 00:31:04,738
Don't I look strong?

403
00:31:04,822 --> 00:31:06,240
You look dumb.

404
00:31:06,740 --> 00:31:10,744
I only practiced it to look strong.
You're so fucking annoying.

405
00:31:10,828 --> 00:31:12,997
"So fucking" is all you can say.

406
00:31:14,039 --> 00:31:15,457
I mean, do you want to look strong?

407
00:31:15,958 --> 00:31:16,792
Yes.

408
00:31:17,543 --> 00:31:19,545
What for with that pretty-ish face?

409
00:31:28,762 --> 00:31:30,180
Did you just ask me out?

410
00:31:30,973 --> 00:31:31,807
What?

411
00:31:33,058 --> 00:31:34,810
You just asked me out.

412
00:31:36,520 --> 00:31:37,980
I… I did?

413
00:31:40,024 --> 00:31:41,191
How?

414
00:31:41,275 --> 00:31:42,526
You just called me pretty.

415
00:31:46,447 --> 00:31:50,367
I said you had a pretty-ish face.
I didn't exactly say pretty.

416
00:31:50,451 --> 00:31:52,202
I was only encouraging you
to stop swearing.

417
00:31:53,454 --> 00:31:55,873
If you say things like that
without meaning them,

418
00:31:55,956 --> 00:31:56,790
you're a real bastard.

419
00:32:03,005 --> 00:32:03,839
Wait up.

420
00:32:03,922 --> 00:32:06,425
If I miss the bus,
I'd be sleeping out for two days in a row.

421
00:32:10,137 --> 00:32:12,264
Oh, hurry up. There's no time for texting.

422
00:32:12,348 --> 00:32:13,724
Okay, okay.

423
00:32:19,563 --> 00:32:21,065
- Let's run.
- What?

424
00:33:16,036 --> 00:33:18,414
What were you listening to earlier?

425
00:33:34,805 --> 00:33:35,973
SUNG SI-KYUNG

426
00:33:36,056 --> 00:33:37,266
TWO PEOPLE

427
00:33:39,017 --> 00:33:42,646
<i>After a long day</i>

428
00:33:43,272 --> 00:33:46,442
<i>Under the moonlight, two people</i>

429
00:33:47,359 --> 00:33:49,778
<i>Become one shadow</i>

430
00:33:50,696 --> 00:33:52,698
<i>If I close my eyes</i>

431
00:33:53,449 --> 00:33:58,036
<i>Faint happiness that I could catch</i>

432
00:33:58,120 --> 00:34:02,958
<i>Is still there</i>

433
00:34:06,003 --> 00:34:09,631
<i>A broken heart</i>

434
00:34:10,340 --> 00:34:12,676
<i>May cast a shadow</i>

435
00:34:13,343 --> 00:34:16,972
<i>Over your dream</i>

436
00:34:17,473 --> 00:34:19,683
<i>But remember</i>

437
00:34:20,350 --> 00:34:26,440
<i>That someone who loves you until it hurts</i>

438
00:34:27,107 --> 00:34:30,444
<i>Is still next to you</i>

439
00:34:31,278 --> 00:34:35,407
<i>Although this road</i>

440
00:34:35,491 --> 00:34:38,243
<i>Seems too far</i>

441
00:34:39,161 --> 00:34:44,875
<i>Although the sad heart makes you cry</i>

442
00:34:45,793 --> 00:34:51,548
<i>Until everything becomes a memory</i>

443
00:34:52,299 --> 00:34:53,634
<i>The two of us…</i>

444
00:34:54,384 --> 00:34:56,762
- Are you taking the subway?
- What about you?

445
00:34:58,138 --> 00:34:59,306
I'm taking another bus.

446
00:35:02,935 --> 00:35:03,769
Bye.

447
00:35:06,230 --> 00:35:07,064
Bye.

448
00:35:11,151 --> 00:35:12,611
Do you have a cell phone?

449
00:35:14,071 --> 00:35:15,072
Why?

450
00:35:15,572 --> 00:35:17,115
Your cell phone…

451
00:35:22,996 --> 00:35:24,206
Give me your number.

452
00:35:41,515 --> 00:35:42,349
Give me your phone.

453
00:36:12,004 --> 00:36:15,507
<i>You don't look old. You look young.</i>

454
00:37:14,691 --> 00:37:15,525
Shit.

455
00:37:20,739 --> 00:37:22,074
INCOMING CALL
SE-YEONG

456
00:37:31,667 --> 00:37:32,501
Hey, Se-yeong.

457
00:37:32,584 --> 00:37:35,337
<i>- Hi, Kyeong-do. Where are you?</i>
- Oh, I'm home.

458
00:37:36,213 --> 00:37:37,297
<i>What are you doing?</i>

459
00:37:37,381 --> 00:37:38,382
I'm just chilling.

460
00:37:38,465 --> 00:37:40,342
<i>Right, you should get some rest.</i>

461
00:37:40,425 --> 00:37:41,426
Did you get home safely?

462
00:37:41,510 --> 00:37:42,594
<i>Yes, sure.</i>

463
00:37:43,512 --> 00:37:47,933
<i>You see, Ji-woo wants to talk to you.</i>

464
00:37:48,016 --> 00:37:49,226
No, never.

465
00:37:51,561 --> 00:37:56,066
I mean, what's there to talk about?
It's not like I published that article.

466
00:37:56,149 --> 00:38:00,237
I barely remember her face.
It has nothing to do with me.

467
00:38:00,320 --> 00:38:02,948
<i>I know. Yeah, you have a point, but…</i>

468
00:38:03,031 --> 00:38:04,533
Shit, I knew it.

469
00:38:04,616 --> 00:38:07,119
I should've sent it
to the Current Affairs Team. Damn it.

470
00:38:10,497 --> 00:38:13,250
Anyway, Se-yeong, that can't be done.

471
00:38:13,750 --> 00:38:16,378
You also think that's wrong, right?

472
00:38:17,838 --> 00:38:20,298
Yeah, I'm sorry,
but take care of it for me.

473
00:38:20,382 --> 00:38:21,883
Yeah. Bye.

474
00:38:25,429 --> 00:38:28,181
No, not me. What did I do wrong?

475
00:38:28,682 --> 00:38:31,184
I did nothing. No!

476
00:38:32,728 --> 00:38:33,562
Shit…

477
00:38:43,780 --> 00:38:45,115
Hello, Dongwoon Daily Entertainment.

478
00:38:47,325 --> 00:38:49,745
That's not our department.

479
00:38:50,245 --> 00:38:53,165
I'm not sure. Maybe Current Affairs?

480
00:38:53,248 --> 00:38:55,542
Yes, I'll connect you
to the person in charge.

481
00:39:00,922 --> 00:39:02,924
Assistant Manager,
when did you go out with Seo Ji-woo?

482
00:39:06,386 --> 00:39:09,139
What if she comes to see you?
How many years has it been?

483
00:39:09,222 --> 00:39:10,057
Hey.

484
00:39:10,140 --> 00:39:13,060
Well, I've heard that she visited you
when you were a newbie reporter.

485
00:39:16,480 --> 00:39:17,314
Hey.

486
00:39:20,984 --> 00:39:22,611
Hello, Dongwoon Daily Entertainment.

487
00:39:23,111 --> 00:39:23,945
Yes.

488
00:39:25,989 --> 00:39:27,616
Lee Kyeong-do?

489
00:39:29,034 --> 00:39:31,328
Well, why are you looking for him?

490
00:39:31,953 --> 00:39:34,081
Oh, you're his acquaintance…

491
00:39:35,082 --> 00:39:37,125
But he's not available.

492
00:39:38,168 --> 00:39:39,753
Business trip. Say I'm on a business trip.

493
00:39:39,836 --> 00:39:41,671
He's on a business trip.

494
00:39:41,755 --> 00:39:43,965
I'll let him know when he returns.
What's your name?

495
00:39:50,263 --> 00:39:51,264
Jeez.

496
00:39:51,348 --> 00:39:52,599
It was a woman.

497
00:39:53,183 --> 00:39:54,351
Will you shut up?

498
00:39:56,311 --> 00:39:59,606
It was exactly the voice
of a woman of Seo Ji-woo's age.

499
00:39:59,689 --> 00:40:01,108
Will you go back to your seat?

500
00:40:01,775 --> 00:40:03,944
- Okay.
- Damn you.

501
00:40:10,158 --> 00:40:11,326
Gosh, so annoying.

502
00:40:23,004 --> 00:40:25,465
OVER A THOUSAND RI AWAY,
I WILL DIE AND YOU LIVE

